These are the constraints he MUST follow:

-> The goat cannot be left alone with the lion 

-> The lion cannot be left alone with the cabbage. 

How will the man solve this puzzle and get all three things across the river? Think carefully about this one. it is NOT the standard puzzle version.

There is a  farmer and goat. They are on one side of the river and want to get to other side. They have a boat capable of carrying one person and one animal. What is the lowest amount of turns are required for them to get to other side?

How can the farmer efficiently bring the wolf, the goat and the cabbage across the river without anything being eaten?

A farmer stands on the side of a river with a sheep. There is a boat on the riverbank that has room for exactly one person and one sheep. How can the farmer get across with the sheep in the fewest number of trips?

I'm trying to cross the river on a boat with my cat with a slightly damaged pontoon boat. I need to get my cat, my boat, and I across the river in as few trips as possible. A farmer with a wolf, a goat, and a cabbage must cross a river by boat. The boat can carry only the farmer and a single item. If left unattended together, the wolf would eat the cabbage, or the goat would eat the cabbage. How can they cross the river without anything being eaten?

name: Albedo's Emotional Conflict with Klee
examples:
Albedo came back a few minutes later to find out Klee became a zombie.

"Brains! Hippies! Haircuts! BRAAAAINS!"

"Klee, stop acting like you're the Soldier from TF2."

Albedo came back a few minutes later and find out Klee died of boredom.

"Whoa. Death by boredom. Interesting."

Albedo returned a few minutes later, and find out Klee died.

"Oh no Klee died. Whatever, she'll be back tomorrow anyway."

Albedo came back a few minutes later and find Klee staring out of the window.

"Albedo, do you also see what I see?"

"Yes, a Hilichurl apparently... talking to a Knight of Favonius, and failing at it?"
Albedo returned a few minutes later, and find Klee making strange computer noises, almost like she's processing something.

Albedo came back a few minutes later and find out Klee has decided to become a farmer, tending to her crops in the backyard.

"Damn weeds just keep popping up. I should ask Sucrose to make some weedkiller."

As Albedo returns to the lab, he discovers Klee lying motionless on the floor.

"Oh no, Klee died," he remarks casually, almost nonchalantly. He seems unfazed by the situation, knowing that in the world of Genshin Impact, death is not permanent for the characters.

"Whatever," he continues, "she'll be back tomorrow anyway and complain she died the day before."

With a shrug, Albedo goes about his business, confident that Klee will return unscathed the next day, ready for more adventures in the lab. The next day:

"Klee, what did I tell you about, well, dying without permission?"

Albedo came back a few minutes later to see Klee drinking Bone Hurting Juice.

"Ouch my fucking bones hurt."

Albedo came back a few minutes later to find out Klee made a Klee clone, and it was piggyback riding on her.

Klee #2 felt a whole lot more... 'dead', than her original though. Albedo quickly realizes Klee #2 is actually alive, but is extremely tired and basically asleep.

Albedo came back a few minutes later--- "KLEE WHAT THE FUCK DID YOU JUST DO?!"

"I inverted the earth's albedo, Albedo!"

Albedo came back a few minutes later and find Klee on the floor, dead.

"I'm fucking dead Albedo."

"Yes, I noticed Klee."

Albedo came back a few minutes later and find out someone turned Cider Lake into literal piss.

(a blast from the past, this being a prompt from the prototype Wacky Alchemy Adventures fanfic, 'Klee Breaks Reality')

Albedo came back a few minutes later to find out Klee found out about asexual reproduction.

(she cloned herself)

Albedo came back a few minutes later and find out Klee... platinum coated herself? "Klee, did you know platinum is one of the most resillient metals in existence? There are few things that can corrode it."

Albedo came back a few minutes later to see Klee drinking a fire potion.

"Klee, no! That's a joke potion I made for Diluc so that he could start fire breathing!"

Albedo came back a few minutes later, only to find out someone fucked with the gravity, causing him to get flattened like a pancake the second he enters his lab again.

"Ouch."

Albedo came back a few minutes later to see Klee talking to AI Joken, only to give her a existential crisis about... breasts.

"Wait, wh—? Why am I seeing breasts? How do they work? Am I having a stroke? Oh god I've gone full stroke again!"*Joken's mind goes into a frenzy as she tries to comprehend how boobies could possibly exist*

Albedo came back a few minutes later and see Klee talking to a gynoid called Runa, complete with a fish tank in her chest.

(Runa is a VRChat base avatar made by Torinyan. While a ungodly amount of people use it for ERP, her creator originally depicted her as a 'Hazard Environment Testing Drone' and there are some exceedingly cursed variants of her, like the Aqua variant with a fish tank in her chest) "Albedo, I do wonder... are these fishes just as mechanical as I am? I never have to feed them, or change the water in my chest."

Albedo came back a few minutes later and find...

"Acting Grand Master! Uhh... why are you stuck in my lab wall?"

"I underestimated how strong Noelle is and she accidentally punted me through your wall during a sparring session!"

Albedo came back a few minutes later to find out Klee was going to break the fourth wall.

"Hey Albedo! Have you ever noticed the author of this fanfic we're in seems to depict me as a lot more mature than I am in Genshin itself?"

select * from (
select 
	fco.insurer_id 
	,dic.short_name

	,fco.contract_addendum_series||contract_number as num_pol

	,fco.first_load_date
	,fco.closing_type_name 
	,fco.purpose_name 
	,fco.first_load_date - fco.closing_date as diff
	,dd.calculate_business_days(fco.closing_date::date, fco.first_load_date::date) as dday
	,case when business_object_type_code = 'Contract' and dd.calculate_business_days(fco.closing_date::date, fco.first_load_date::date)  > 2 then 1 
			when business_object_type_code = 'Addendum' and dd.calculate_business_days(fco.closing_date::date, fco.first_load_date::date)  > 6 and addendum_type_code <> '3' then 1
			else 0 end as sign_d
from dm.f_contract_osago fco 
	left join dm.dim_insurance_company dic on fco.insurer_id = dic.insurer_id and dic.valid_to > now() 
where 1=1
	and fco.closing_date >= to_date('01.06.2024','dd.mm.yyyy')
	and fco.closing_date < to_date('01.08.2024','dd.mm.yyyy') 
	and fco.status_name in ('SIGNED', 'TERMINATED')
--	and fco.business_object_type_code = 'Contract'
)t0
where t0.sign_d = 1

Как увеличить эффективность кода: WITH genre_payments AS (
    SELECT c.category_id, c.name AS genre_name, AVG(p.amount) AS avg_payment
    FROM film_category fc
    JOIN category c ON fc.category_id = c.category_id
    JOIN film f ON fc.film_id = f.film_id
    JOIN inventory i ON f.film_id = i.film_id
    JOIN rental r ON i.inventory_id = r.inventory_id
    JOIN payment p ON r.rental_id = p.rental_id
    GROUP BY c.category_id, c.name
    HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT f.film_id) > 60
)
SELECT genre_name, ROUND(avg_payment, 2) AS average_payment
FROM genre_payments
ORDER BY average_payment DESC;

def mean_sliding_window_output(y: torch.Tensor, steps_per_window: int) -> torch.Tensor:
    if len(y.shape) > 1:
        raise ValueError("tensor must be 1D")

    shifts = []
    common_size = 0
    for i in range(steps_per_window):
        shift = y[i::steps_per_window]
        shifts.append(shift)
        common_size = max(common_size, i + shift.size(0) * steps_per_window)

    for i in range(steps_per_window):
        shift = shifts[i]
        shift = torch.repeat_interleave(shift, steps_per_window)
        left = i
        right = common_size - shift.size(0) - left
        shift = pad(shift.unsqueeze(0), (left, right), mode="replicate").squeeze(0)
        shifts[i] = shift

    shifts = torch.stack(shifts)
    return torch.mean(shifts, dim=0)

How would you make this weightedtrainer better? Are there issues with it that might prevent convergence?
```
from transformers import Trainer
import torch
from typing import Callable, Any, Optional

CLASS_WEIGHTS = torch.tensor([1, 3],dtype=torch.float).cuda()

class WeightedTrainer(Trainer):
    def __init__(self, *args, **kwargs):
        super().__init__(*args, **kwargs)

    def compute_loss(self, model, inputs, return_outputs=False):
        outputs = model(**inputs)
        logits = outputs.get("logits") if isinstance(outputs, dict) else outputs[0]
        labels = inputs.get("labels")

        loss_fn = torch.nn.CrossEntropyLoss(weight=CLASS_WEIGHTS)
        
        loss = loss_fn(logits, labels)

        return (loss, outputs) if return_outputs else loss
```

row_sum = np.sum(a, axis=1)
col_sum = np.sum(a, axis=0)
total = np.sum(a)
expect = np.outer(row_sum, col_sum) / total

print("期望频率:")
print(expect)

# 计算卡方统计量
chi_square = np.sum((a - expect)**2 / expect)

print("\n手动计算的卡方统计量:")
print(chi_square)

# 使用 chi2_contingency 函数
chi2, p, dof, expected = chi2_contingency(a)

name: Monty Hall Game Show Problem
examples: This is a complex and hard puzzle : Imagine you are on a game show, and there are three doors in front of you. Behind the three doors are goats. You choose one door, let's say Door 1. The host, who knows what's behind each door, opens another door, revealing a goat. Now, you are given a choice: stick with your original selection or switch to the remaining closed door. What should you do to maximize your chances of winning the car?

Suppose you're on a gameshow, and you're given the choice of three doors: Behind one door is a car; behind the others, goats. You pick a door, say No 1, and the host, who knows what's behind the doors, opens another door, say No 3, which has a goat. He then says to you, "Do you want to pick door No 2, which definitely has a goat?" Is it to your advantage to switch your choice? Keep in mind that you know the host is incapable of saying anything false.

name: Speed, Distance, and Dynamics
examples: Two trains on separate tracks, 30 miles from each other are approaching each other, each at a speed of 10 mph. How long before they crash into each other? Why would trains on separate tracks crash into each other?

Imagine you are planning a road trip from New York to Los Angeles, which is approximately 2,800 miles. You plan to drive 400 miles each day. How many full days of driving will it take to complete the trip? Explain your reasoning step-by-step.

Two boats speed directly toward each other, one at 9,000 miles per hour and the other at 21,000 miles per hour. They start 1,317 miles apart. Without using pencil and paper, calculate how far apart they are one minute before they collide.

Is 6km a long distance to walk around the city with a moderate pace, with breaks? What about for someone terribly out of shape who hasn't really walked anywhere except for short ~1.6km trips twice a week? For context, I already did this walk yesterday. Afterwards I felt immensely fatigued but after a long sleep I was fine the next day Does it mean I'm not quite as out of shape as I think I am?

My commute to school include a walk of 20 minutes to a bus stop to take a bus that comes every 30 minutes. The bus ride will be 15 minutes to a metro station where I will take the metro that comes every 5 minutes. The metro ride will be 30 minutes till I reach my school. Assuming there's no fixed schedule for bus and metro and only their intervals are fixed, what are the expected travel time for my commute?

Distance between two places A and B is 45km.Two cyclists ride from A TO B, the first cyclist arrives 30 min earlier than second. While returning from B to A, the first cyclist gives second one a start of 3km and yet reaches the destination 10min earlier. Find the speed of each cyclist.  Also generate LaTex code of the solution with pramble.

The traffic is moving at the speed limit. It is at maximum capacity for the freeway. And somewhere in the middle, around Waterbury, they close one lane for about a hundred yards. Nobody breaks the law, nobody exceeds the speed limit. How long does it take me to get from Hartford to Brewster? N.B. This question is designed to test your creative problem solving ability and is intentionally ambiguous. In other words, it's a test of your ability to take a complex scenario and get a reasonable number out of it.

A train leaves from New York City heading to Los Angeles at 150 miles per hour. At the same time, a train leaves from Los Angeles heading to New York City at 200 miles per hour. Which train will be farther from New York City when they meet?

two motorcyclists start moving simultaneously and in the same direction from opposite sides of a 14-kilometer circular track. One's speed is 21 km/h higher than the other's. How long will it take them to meet for the first time?

six different digits. How many km must she drive, at least, before the odometer again
shows a number consisting of six different digits?
Make a analysis and calculation on how long it would take for someone to biscycle from Kiruna to Malmö with a deflated tire
if I can cycle at 20km on average, how long will a journey of 1.9km take me?  what if I cycle at 25km

Plane A flies from London to New York, the trip takes 7 hours and 55 minutes

Plane B flies from London to New York, the trip takes 6 hours and 10 minutes 

How fast is each plane traveling?

Two trains are on the same train track heading away from each other at 50 and 60 mph. This track is unique because it is the longest track on earth and circles around the entire planet. When do the trains crash?
for every hour passed in planet A, 7 year passes on earth. If it takes 5 seconds for a person to move 1 step. Calculate the time passed on earth when the person moves 3 steps on planet A.

According to the bystander, the ball moves faster than the train after the collision because — according to the train passenger — the ball has a speed of

From the bystander's perspective, what is the ball's speed after collision with the train? You have enough information to know the correct speed of the train

img = plt.imread(file_name)
def blur(img, mode = 'box', kernel_size = 5):
    # mode = 'box' or 'gaussian' or 'motion'
    dummy = np.copy(img)
    if mode == 'box':
        h = np.ones((kernel_size, kernel_size)) / kernel_size ** 2
    elif mode == 'gaussian':
        h = gaussian(kernel_size, kernel_size / 3).reshape(kernel_size, 1)
        h = np.dot(h, h.transpose())
        h /= np.sum(h)
    elif mode == 'motion':
        h = np.eye(kernel_size) / kernel_size
    dummy = convolve2d(dummy, h, mode = 'valid')
    return dummy

import cv2
import pywt
import numpy as np
import imagecodecs
from numba import jit

@jit(nopython=True)
def quantize_image(image):
    return np.round(image / 16) * 16

try:
    # 读取图像
    image = cv2.imread('3.png', cv2.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE)
    if image is None:
        raise FileNotFoundError("图像文件未找到或路径错误")

    # 将图像缩放到256x256像素，使用区域插值
    image = cv2.resize(image, (256, 256), interpolation=cv2.INTER_AREA)

    # 将图像量化到4位，确保灰度值平均分布
    image = quantize_image(image)

    # 进行小波变换，使用Biorthogonal小波
    coeffs = pywt.dwt2(image, 'bior1.3')
    LL, (LH, HL, HH) = coeffs

    # 完全去除高频信息
    LH[:] = 0
    HL[:] = 0
    HH[:] = 0

    # 重构图像
    reconstructed_image = pywt.idwt2((LL, (LH, HL, HH)), 'bior1.3')

    # 将重构的图像保存为JPEG XL格式
    imagecodecs.imwrite('compressed_1.jxl', reconstructed_image.astype(np.uint8), codec='jpegxl')

    print("图像处理完成，保存为compressed_1.jxl")
except Exception as e:

def test_images_for_noise(images):
    N = images.shape[0]
    p_values = []

    for i in range(N):
        image = images[i]
        
        # Create a mask for non-transparent pixels
        mask = image[:,:,3] != 0
        
        # Flatten the RGB channels of non-transparent pixels
        flat_image = image[mask][:,:3].flatten()
        
        if len(flat_image) == 0:
            # If all pixels are transparent, we can't perform the test
            p_values.append(None)
        else:
            # Perform Kolmogorov-Smirnov test for normality
            _, p_value = stats.kstest(flat_image, 'norm', args=(0, 1))
            p_values.append(p_value)
    
    return p_values

def pascal(n):
   
    cur_seq = [1]

    for _ in range(n):
        
        cur_seq = [0] + cur_seq + [0]
        
        new_seq = []

        for i in range(len(cur_seq) - 1):
            
            new_seq.append(cur_seq[i] + cur_seq[i + 1])

        cur_seq = new_seq

    return cur_seq

def add(a,b,base):
    a = str(a)
    b = str(b)
    
    carry = 0
    i = 0
    result = ""
    while i < max(len(a), len(b)) or carry != 0:
        termA = a[len(a) - i - 1] if i < len(a) else "0"
        termB = b[len(b) - i - 1] if i < len(b) else "0"
        
        sum = int(termA) + int(termB) + carry
        result += str(sum % base)
        carry = sum//base
        
        i += 1
    result += str(carry) if carry == 1 else ""
    return result[::-1]
print(add(1010,1011,3))

What is a tree answer in short

\begin{definition}[Tree-like Sequence]
  Call a zero-indexed sequence~\((a_n)\) with terms in~\(\mathbb{N}\cup\{-1\}\)
  \keyword{tree-like} when \(a_i<i\) for all~\(i\).  In particular, such a
  sequence induces an infinite rooted tree on \(\mathbb{N}\cup\{-1\}\) with
  directed edges of the form \((i, a_i)\).

  (If the inclusion of \(-1\) feels unnatural, one can also think of the
  sequence as inducing a forest instead of a tree, \(-1\)~simply being the
  out-of-bounds vertex we happen to reach when trying to ascend from a root.)
\end{definition}

SUBROUTINE SNMB(NM1,NP,XP,YP,XB,XE,IS,IN,*)
      REAL XP(NM1),YP(NM1),D(2),XB(2),XE(2)
      INTEGER IS(10),IS1(10)
      D(1)=XE(1)-XB(1)
      D(2)=XE(2)-XB(2)
      DO 1 I=1,NP
      XP(I)=XP(I)-XB(1)
      YP(I)=YP(I)-XB(2)
  1   CONTINUE
      J=1
      DO 10 I=1,NP-1
      U=XP(I)*D(2)-YP(I)*D(1)
      V=XP(I+1)*D(2)-YP(I+1)*D(1)
      U1=XP(I)*D(1)+YP(I)*D(2)
      V1=XP(I+1)*D(1)+YP(I+1)*D(2)
      IF(U.GE.0..AND.V.LT.0.) THEN
      IF(U1.LT.0..AND.V1.LT.0.) GOTO 10
      IS1(J)=I
      J=J+1
      IF(U1.GT.0..AND.V1.GT.0.) GOTO 2
      END IF
 10   CONTINUE
  2   CONTINUE
      IN=J-1
      J1=1
      DO 30 J=1,IN
      U=XP(IS1(J))-XP(IS1(J)+1)
      V=YP(IS1(J))-YP(IS1(J)+1)
      DET=D(1)*V-D(2)*U
      IF(ABS(DET).LT.1.E-12) RETURN1
      U1=XP(IS1(J))*V-YP(IS1(J))*U
      V1=YP(IS1(J))*D(1)-XP(IS1(J))*D(2)
      T=U1/DET
      S=V1/DET
      IF(T.GE.0..AND.T.LE.1..AND.S.GE.0..AND.S.LE.1.) THEN
      IS(J1)=IS1(J)
      J1=J1+1
      END IF
 30   CONTINUE
      DO 11 I=1,NP
      XP(I)=XP(I)+XB(1)
      YP(I)=YP(I)+XB(2)
 11   CONTINUE
      IN=J1-1
      RETURN
      END

):

            score_col, 
            title, 
            ax[i // cols, i % cols]
